<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="109">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">Carapace</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Pseudochthonius ramalho sp. nov., male A carapace dorsal view, and detail of the anterior margin (with the epistome) B right chelicera (dorsal view) C detail of the rallum D coxa I and II E details of coxal spines F leg I (lateral view) G leg IV (lateral view)." figureDoi="10.3897/subtbiol.40.77451.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/614225" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">7A</figureCitation>
): Carapace 1.09
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than broad, posteriorly constricted, chaetotaxy 4:4:4:2:2 (16), one preocular microseta on each side; eyes absent on male and a tiny eyespot on female; anterior margin distinctly serrate with median denticles larger than lateral ones; epistome prominent and dentate (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Pseudochthonius ramalho sp. nov., male A carapace dorsal view, and detail of the anterior margin (with the epistome) B right chelicera (dorsal view) C detail of the rallum D coxa I and II E details of coxal spines F leg I (lateral view) G leg IV (lateral view)." figureDoi="10.3897/subtbiol.40.77451.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/614225" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">7A-C</figureCitation>
); 3 lyrifissures anteriorly, 1 medially and 2 posteriorly.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="109">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">Abdomen</emphasis>
: Chaetotaxy of tergites I-XI: ♂, 4: 4: 4: 4: 6: 6: 6: 6: 6: 5: 3; ♀, 4: 4: 4: 4: 5: 6: 6: 6: 6: 5: 3. Chaetotaxy of sternites III-XI: (♂/♀) 12: 13: 8: 8: 8: 8: 6: 5: 2, anal cone 0/2 setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="109">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">Genital area</emphasis>
: Anterior genital operculum with 8 (♂), 9 (♀) marginal and discal setae, arranged triangularly in male, with 7-8 unmodified marginal setae on each side; posterior operculum with 6 setae in female.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="109">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">Coxae</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Pseudochthonius ramalho sp. nov., male A carapace dorsal view, and detail of the anterior margin (with the epistome) B right chelicera (dorsal view) C detail of the rallum D coxa I and II E details of coxal spines F leg I (lateral view) G leg IV (lateral view)." figureDoi="10.3897/subtbiol.40.77451.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/614225" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">7D, E</figureCitation>
): Manducatory process distally acute, with 2 setae; pedipalpal coxa with 3 setae, coxa I and II with 4-5 setae on anterior margin and 3-5 highly dented coxal spines in decreasing size distally, coxa III with 7 setae and coxa IV with 8 setae; intercoxal tubercle absent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="109">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">Legs</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Pseudochthonius ramalho sp. nov., male A carapace dorsal view, and detail of the anterior margin (with the epistome) B right chelicera (dorsal view) C detail of the rallum D coxa I and II E details of coxal spines F leg I (lateral view) G leg IV (lateral view)." figureDoi="10.3897/subtbiol.40.77451.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/614225" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">7F, G</figureCitation>
): Typical of the genus (
<bibRefCitation author="Chamberlin, JC" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de la Societe Zoologique de France" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" pagination="173 - 179" refId="B12" refString="Chamberlin, JC, 1929. The genus Pseudochthonius Balzan (Arachnida - Chelonetida). Bulletin de la Societe Zoologique de France 54: 173 - 179" title="The genus Pseudochthonius Balzan (Arachnida - Chelonetida)." volume="54" year="1929">Chamberlin 1929</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
